# Skill structure lock

After the directory-wide refactor, the three pipeline skills share one structure.
When fixing bugs or updating behavior, **edit inside that pattern** — do not invent a new layout.

## Do

- Change required behavior in the existing step, checklist item, or owning reference file
- Update links if a file is renamed within the standard folders
- Keep the shared SKILL.md skeleton (frontmatter, checklist, numbered phases, `→` links)

## Do not

- Create parallel folder schemes (`references/`, `docs/` inside a skill, ad-hoc top-level dirs)
- Reshuffle the shared runbook skeleton just to emphasize one fix
- Split or merge classified folders (`protocol/`, `notion/`, `contracts/`, `domain/`, `indexes/`) without an explicit user request to change the standard

If a structural change to the shared pattern is truly required, ask the user first.
